{"page_id": 32749, "slug": "Neon_Genesis_Evangelion_RPG:_The_Nerv_White_Paper", "title": "Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper", "display_title": "<span class=\"mw-page-title-main\">Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper</span>", "namespace": 0, "content_model": "wikitext", "language": null, "wikitext": "{{Publication\n| image       = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper coverslip-frontonly.jpg|200px]]\n| title          = Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper\n| alt_title       = \n| author       = Various\n| pub_date       = April 20, 1996\n| publisher         = Kadokawa Shoten\n| pages        = 138 + 20 pages of cards.\n| dimensions        = 10.2 x 7.3 x 0.6 in\n| ISBN = 4-04-714513-0\n}}\n\n'''Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper''' is a card-based role playing game. The first 138 pages contain rules and various story inserts and the book's back cover can be used (cut out) as a box to store the cards, which are printed on the last 20 pages of the book (also requires to be cut out). The book also contains a fold out page which acts as the game board, a map of [[Tokyo-3]].\n\nThe story inserts contain an [[Extracanonical Character]] named [[Extracanonical_Characters#Marie_Vincennes|Marie Vincennes]], a 14 year old [[Evangelion]] pilot with a PhD. It also contains 2 [[Extracanonical Mecha|Extracanonical Angels]] named [[Extracanonical_Mecha#Iblis_.28.E3.82.A4.E3.83.96.E3.83.AA.E3.83.BC.E3.82.B9.29|Iblis]] and [[Extracanonical_Mecha#Barakijal_.28.E3.83.90.E3.83.A9.E3.82.AD.E3.82.A8.E3.83.AB.29|Barakijal]].\n\nThe game consists of ''events'' and ''battles''; each character has 2 attributes (''harmonics'' being one of them). The GM is always [[Gendo Ikari]].\n\nA fan translation by Trotti is [https://archive.org/details/eva-rpg-nerv-white-paper-english/page/n9/mode/2up available here].\n\n{{-}}\n<center>\n{{MontageBox\n|float   = middle\n|columns = 4\n|title   = Story and Background\n|image1 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image2 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image3 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image4 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image5 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_014.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image6 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_015.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image7 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_016.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image8 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_017.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image9 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_018.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image10 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_019.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image11 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_020.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image12 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_021.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image13 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_022.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image14 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_023.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image15 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_024.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image16 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_025.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image17 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_050.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|caption =\n}}\n{{-}}\n{{MontageBox\n|float   = middle\n|columns = 4\n|title   = \"The Dead Sea Scrolls - Main Subject\" (Marie Vincennes and Angels)\n|image1 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_078.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image2 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_080.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image3 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_088.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image4 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_091.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image5 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_094.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image6 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_097.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image7 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_103.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image8 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_107.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image9 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_108.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image10 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_110.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image11 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_120.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image12 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_126.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image13 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_128.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|caption =\n}}\n{{-}}\n{{MontageBox\n|float   = middle\n|columns = 4\n|title   = The Cards and Cover\n|image1 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_146.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image2 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_151.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image3 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_154.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image4 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_155.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image5 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_foldout.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image6 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_cover-front.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|image7 = [[Image:Nge-rpg-white-paper_cover-back.jpg|thumb|150px]]\n|caption =\n}}\n</center>\n{{-}}\n\n\n{{Pub List}}\n\n[[Category:A to Z]]\n[[Category:Publications]]", "html": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><table class=\"infobox\" style=\"width: 200; text-align: left; font-size: 100%;\" cellspacing=\"2\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\" width=\"150px\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/File:Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/f/fc/Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg/200px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"200\" height=\"259\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fc/Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg/300px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fc/Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg/400px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_coverslip-frontonly.jpg 2x\" /></a></span>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th width=\"200px\">Title\n</th>\n<td>Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr>\n<th>Author\n</th>\n<td>Various\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Original Publication Date\n</th>\n<td>April 20, 1996\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Publisher\n</th>\n<td>Kadokawa Shoten\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<th>Pages\n</th>\n<td>138 + 20 pages of cards.\n</td></tr>\n\n<tr>\n<th>Dimensions\n</th>\n<td>10.2 x 7.3 x 0.6 in\n</td></tr>\n\n\n<tr>\n<th>ISBN\n</th>\n<td>4-04-714513-0\n</td></tr></tbody></table>\n<p><b>Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper</b> is a card-based role playing game. The first 138 pages contain rules and various story inserts and the book's back cover can be used (cut out) as a box to store the cards, which are printed on the last 20 pages of the book (also requires to be cut out). The book also contains a fold out page which acts as the game board, a map of <a href=\"/Tokyo-3\" title=\"Tokyo-3\">Tokyo-3</a>.\n</p><p>The story inserts contain an <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Character\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Extracanonical Character\">Extracanonical Character</a> named <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Characters#Marie_Vincennes\" title=\"Extracanonical Characters\">Marie Vincennes</a>, a 14 year old <a href=\"/Evangelion\" title=\"Evangelion\">Evangelion</a> pilot with a PhD. It also contains 2 <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Mecha\" title=\"Extracanonical Mecha\">Extracanonical Angels</a> named <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Mecha#Iblis_.28.E3.82.A4.E3.83.96.E3.83.AA.E3.83.BC.E3.82.B9.29\" title=\"Extracanonical Mecha\">Iblis</a> and <a href=\"/Extracanonical_Mecha#Barakijal_.28.E3.83.90.E3.83.A9.E3.82.AD.E3.82.A8.E3.83.AB.29\" title=\"Extracanonical Mecha\">Barakijal</a>.\n</p><p>The game consists of <i>events</i> and <i>battles</i>; each character has 2 attributes (<i>harmonics</i> being one of them). The GM is always <a href=\"/Gendo_Ikari\" title=\"Gendo Ikari\">Gendo Ikari</a>.\n</p><p>A fan translation by Trotti is <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://archive.org/details/eva-rpg-nerv-white-paper-english/page/n9/mode/2up\">available here</a>.\n</p><p><br clear=\"all\" />\n</p>\n<center>\n<table style=\"float: middle; clear: middle; width: 1px; text-align: center; vertical-align: center; font-size: 90%; background-color: white; border: 1px solid #aaaaaa; margin: 1em;\" cellpadding=\"2\" cellspacing=\"0\" border=\"0\">\n\n<tbody><tr>\n<td style=\"background: tan; font-size: 120%; text-align: center\" colspan=\"4\"><b>Story and Background</b>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><figure typeof=\"mw:File/Thumb\"><a href=\"/File:Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/f/f4/Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg/150px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"206\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/f4/Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg/225px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/f4/Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg/300px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_010.jpg 2x\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure></td>\n<td><figure typeof=\"mw:File/Thumb\"><a href=\"/File:Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/b/b5/Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg/150px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"207\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/b/b5/Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg/225px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/b/b5/Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg/300px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_011.jpg 2x\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure></td>\n<td><figure typeof=\"mw:File/Thumb\"><a href=\"/File:Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg/150px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"209\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/7/7e/Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg/225px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/7/7e/Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg/300px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_012.jpg 2x\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure></td>\n<td><figure typeof=\"mw:File/Thumb\"><a href=\"/File:Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg\" class=\"mw-file-description\"><img src=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg/150px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"150\" height=\"206\" class=\"mw-file-element\" srcset=\"/images/thumb/f/fd/Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg/225px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg 1.5x, /images/thumb/f/fd/Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg/300px-Nge-rpg-white-paper_013.jpg 2x\" /></a><figcaption></figcaption></figure>\n</td></tr>\n<tr>\n<td><fig