n time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   16.509      1 -total\n 53.31%    8.801      3 Template:MontageBox\n 17.89%    2.953      1 Template:Publication\n 13.61%    2.248      5 Template:-\n 10.15%    1.675      1 Template:Pub_List\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key mediawikidb-ew_:pcache:idhash:32749-0!canonical and timestamp 20260417145031 and revision id 117400. Rendering was triggered because: api-parse\n -->\n</div>", "summary": "Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper is a card-based role playing game. The first 138 pages contain rules and various story inserts and the book's back cover can be used (cut out) as a box to store the cards, which are printed on the last 20 pages of the book (also requires to be cut out). The book also contains a fold out page which acts as the game board, a map of Tokyo-3.", "sections": [], "categories": ["A to Z", "Publications"], "infobox": {}, "templates": ["-", "MontageBox", "Pub List", "Publication"], "internal_links": ["Extracanonical_Characters", "Evangelion", "Gendo Ikari", "Tokyo-3", "Extracanonical_Mecha", "Extracanonical Character", "Extracanonical Mecha"], "external_links": ["https://archive.org/details/eva-rpg-nerv-white-paper-english/page/n9/mode/2up"], "iw_links": [], "lang_links": [], "properties": [], "protection": [], "rev_id": 117400, "length_bytes": null, "parse_warnings": [], "touched_at": null, "references": [], "chunks": [{"article_slug": "Neon_Genesis_Evangelion_RPG:_The_Nerv_White_Paper", "section": "", "content": "Neon Genesis Evangelion RPG: The Nerv White Paper is a card-based role playing game. The first 138 pages contain rules and various story inserts and the book's back cover can be used (cut out) as a box to store the cards, which are printed on the last 20 pages of the book (also requires to be cut out). The book also contains a fold out page which acts as the game board, a map of Tokyo-3.\n\nThe story inserts contain an Extracanonical Character named Marie Vincennes, a 14 year old Evangelion pilot with a PhD. It also contains 2 Extracanonical Angels named Iblis and Barakijal.\n\nThe game consists of events and battles; each character has 2 attributes (harmonics being one of them). The GM is always Gendo Ikari.\n\nA fan translation by Trotti is available here.\n\nCategory:A to Z\nCategory:Publications", "position": 0, "token_count": 193}]}